The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Dubai, June 14 (PTI): Fourteen Indian sailors who were taken hostage by Somali pirates for 10 days have been rescued by a Nato warship off the coast of Somalia.          
	Ismail Abdurehman, the captain of the hijacked dhow Visvakalyan, said the pirates attacked the vessel carrying a shipment of charcoal from Mogadishu to Sharjah on June 3. Six pirates armed with AK-47s and a rocket-propelled grenade launcher approached the dhow in a high-speed skiff.                   
	 Solan, Himachal Pradesh (PTI): Three teachers of a government school have been arrested for tonsuring the heads of 17 students who failed to answer some questions. A local court released the teachers on bail against a personal bond of Rs 10,000 each. Police on Saturday arrested the trio on the basis of complaints by parents.                   
	 Delhi (PTI): Parliamentary affairs minister Pawan Kumar Bansal has been given additional charge of the water resources ministry, which was held by Speaker Meira Kumar. Pratik Prakashbapu Patil has been appointed minister of state for youth affairs and sports.                   
	 Panvel, Raigad (PTI): A Panvel court has remanded NCP leader Padamsinh Patil in CBI custody till June 20 after the agency said it wanted to conduct more investigations. The CBI also said it wanted to conduct narco tests on Patil, arrested for the murder of Congress leader Pawanraje Nimbalkar.                                                                                                                           
